HEADWORD: Arenaceous
<hw>Ar`e*na"ceous</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>arenaceus</ets>, fr. <ets>arena</ets> sand.]</ety> <def>Sandy or
consisting largely of sand; of the nature of sand; easily disintegrating
into sand; friable; <as>as, <ex>arenaceous</ex>
limestone</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arenarious</ent>⟦br⟧
